race.comment: ABENDER (6) may be the best of the three Gollan runners.Was outgraded in the rich Rising Stars on the Gold Coast, but his form leading into that reads extra well for this. Flies this course and distance and Maloney continues his association with the gelding. Finally draws a low barrier and he can break back. JOPPA LANE (4) was well beaten in the same contest, but impressed beaten a whisker at Eagle Farm this trip on resumption in a 70. Proven third-up and is capable of sitting closer. Has more up the sleeve and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. JENCHICK BOOM (13) resumed for Gollan further improved when narrowly beaten at Ipswich. Goes second-up and from a handy barrier Jones will give her every chance. Stablemate BLUE ALLURE (10) always puts in an dug deep to win a CL2 at the Sunshine Coast her latest.
